<p><strong>Golden Halberd</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Halberds" href="/Halberds" target="">Halberd</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Golden Halberd</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for dealing <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Holy Damage" href="/Holy+Damage" target="">Holy Damage</a> in addition to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Physical Damage" href="/Physical+Damage" target="">Physical Damage</a> during combat. It is complemented with the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golden Vow" href="/Golden+Vow" target="">Golden Vow</a> Skill that increases the attack power and defense stats of the user, as well as allies within range.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Weighty halberd forged of gold. Wielded by the Order of Tree Sentinels, heavily equipped knights.&nbsp;<br>Deals holy damage.</em></p> 
 <p><em>A masterfully crafted weapon that lives up to its heft, but is difficult for one mere human strength to wield.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Golden Halberd in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The <strong>Golden Halberd</strong> weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Drops from the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Tree Sentinel" href="/Tree+Sentinel" target="">Tree Sentinel</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Limgrave" href="/Limgrave" target="">Limgrave</a>. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2052&amp;lat=-193.265&amp;lng=101.0084&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2052&amp;lat=-193.265&amp;lng=101.0084&amp;zoom=8">Elden Ring Map here</a>]</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Golden Halberd Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Golden Vow" href="/Golden+Vow" target="">Golden Vow</a>.</li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a> nor buffed with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic" href="/Magic" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Golden Halberd</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Other notes go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
