				<li id="16686308" class="cmnt-root" data="6" data-d="1652756966000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578240/Golden-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">16 May 2022 23:09</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16686308" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">When I first got this halberd, for some reason I immediately assumed it would be mediocre at best. This thing is an absolute beast, for one simple reason: it hits HARD. Sure it&apos;s split damage, but by RL 150 it can reach an unbuffed AR of over 900 with the right build, which is absolutely insane for an halberd. Its ash of war is not customizable, but it will bump the AR even higher, while also granting some damage absorbtion. Also, this thing seems to deal higher poise damage than most other halberd, while being just as fast. If you&apos;re running a STR/FAI build, I definitely recommend checking this out.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16686308" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16686308" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="