				<li id="16675737" class="cmnt-root" data="20" data-d="1652192749000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578240/Golden-Halberd" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">10 May 2022 10:25</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16675737" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I absolutely adore this halberd. I initially made a memey cosplay build of the Tree Sentinel, primarily using it. I didn&apos;t expect much, but as time went on I found that it was rather powerful. <br/><br/>Here&apos;s why:<br/><br/>PROS<br/><br/>- One-handed running attack into one-handed L1 is (potentially) a true combo if the enemy panic rolls out of stagger. <br/><br/>- Take this with a grain of salt, as I&apos;m not knowledgeable on the proper workings of the poise system, but the Golden Halberd seems to deal immense poise damage, especially at higher upgrade levels. In testing with a friend that had a poise of 73 I was able to consistently stagger him with every move in its set. Again, take this with a grain of salt, this is just some empirical evidence I&apos;ve gathered.<br/><br/>- One and two-handed running attacks EXCEL at rollcatching, as the hit box on the head of the halberd lingers for a significant amount of time after the initial thrust. Excellent for players that prefer to rush down and pressure their enemies.<br/><br/>- Its moves are, at least on a relatively scale to other weapons of its size and/or class, very fast to come out and very quick to recover from. With the exception of heavy attacks, you can safely throw out moves with thing weapon and often still have time to evade a counterattack.<br/><br/>- Somewhat minor, but since its Ash of War is Golden Vow, it saves me a slot when equipping other buff incants for fights, slightly saving time on having to scroll through all of them.<br/><br/>- If building for Strength and Faith, this weapon is for you, and has the added bonus of working in a bestial incant build, since the clawmark seal scales well with both stats as well.<br/><br/>CONS<br/><br/>- Does not work well with low poise. While its moves are fast and non-committal, that speed it relative to halberds and larger weapons. Smaller weapons such as straight-swords, katanas, thrusting swords, etc. will still be able to punish your attacks. Thus, having high poise to compensate is recommended.<br/><br/>- No Ash of War customization, nor buffs/infusiions. While Golden Vow is an amazing buff to have constant access to, regardless of build provided the faith req is met, not being able to flesh out the weapon with other moves, is a definite dissapointment. That, and not being able to infuse it to adapt it into other builds.<br/><br/>-Take this with a grain of salt, but at least in the case of my rushdown-focused playstyle, this weapon utterly devours stamina. Pack a turtleneck or watch your stamina management more carefully when using this. It really could just be me, but if you do decide to use this weapon, be sure to feel it our for yourself, and act accordingly.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16675737" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16675737" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>23</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>3</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16675737"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16675737" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16675737"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
